  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] There was-- there was one exhibit that we had that was admitted into evidence, and I have a copy of it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was Dr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Sigmund Rascher, who was so instrumental in-- in these experiments, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] who was not tried because he was ultimately executed with his wife by-- at Hitler's order, for other reasons.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But he submitted a report that I-- I refer to in my presentations.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Quote, 'It was a continuous experiment without oxygen, at a height of 12 kilometers, which is 39,000 feet, conducted on a 37-year-old Jew in good general condition.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Breathing continued up to 30 minutes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "After four minutes, the experimental subject began to perspire and wiggle his head.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "After five minutes, cramps occurred.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Between six and ten minutes, breathing increased in speed, and the experimental subject became unconscious.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "From 11 to 30 minutes, breathing slowed down to three breaths per minute, finally stopping altogether.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Severe cyanosis developed in between, and foam appeared at the mouth.' Unquote.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "This was just one of the exhibits that was admitted in evidence.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a captured German document.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the Nazis had, fortunately, for the purpose of these trials, meticulously recorded by documentation, film, and photography, almost all of their atrocities, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] whether they were in the medical case or the other cases.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because tens of thousands of pieces of documentary evidence had been captured by the British and US and Allied forces, most of the facts presented at these trials were incapable of being denied or defended.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in the Doctors' Trial, there were 85 witnesses or victims who testified, and there were 1,471 pieces of documentary evidence admitted into evidence.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
